        {
          "username": "Syed Haider",
          "rating": 1,
          "contributor_id": "108782931800858902142",
          "user_review_count": 15,
          "user_photo_count": 1,
          "user_thumbnail": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocL9W7KwWfLg0yoTlZk3jMqZ1larIFjxmbwLPKzOtIedfxzdeQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba12-br100",
          "description": "I visited NYU Kimmel Pavilion recently to see a family member, and I was deeply disappointed by the treatment my family and I received. The reception staff, particularly Kristine, were both disrespectful and discriminatory. It was clear that their behavior was racially biased, which made our visit incredibly uncomfortable and distressing.\n\nManagement needs to address this issue immediately. It is unacceptable for any facility, especially one associated with a prestigious institution like NYU, to tolerate such ignorance and disrespect. I urge the management to take serious steps to hire and train staff who uphold values of respect and inclusivity.\n\nThis experience has left a negative impression, and I hope that changes will be made to ensure that others do not face the same mistreatment.",
